# Production port 3001

PM2 app `darulquran-next` listens on **0.0.0.0:3001**. Apache at darulquran.pk → `http://127.0.0.1:3001/`.

**Not configurable in production.** `deploy/runtime.cjs` forces port **3001** when `NODE_ENV=production`. Never use port **3000**.

| Layer | File |
|-------|------|
| Source of truth | `deploy/runtime.cjs` |
| npm dev/start | `scripts/run-next.mjs` |
| PM2 | `ecosystem.config.cjs` |
| Reverse proxy | `deploy/apache.conf.example`, `deploy/nginx.conf.example` |
| CI health check | `.github/workflows/deploy.yml` |

Changing the port requires updating **all** rows plus `.env.example` and server `.env`.

Deploy workflow → `11-deploy-ops.mdc`
